    <item>
      <title>Grooming Tips for My Dog?</title>
      <link>http://www.funnydogsvideos.com/1728/grooming-tips-for-my-dog/</link>
      <comments>http://www.funnydogsvideos.com/1728/grooming-tips-for-my-dog/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Tue, 05 Jun 2012 10:55:05 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>lynn</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Dog Grooming]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.funnydogsvideos.com/1728/grooming-tips-for-my-dog/</guid>
      <description>I have a yorkshire terrier and of course she needs to be groomed but she&amp;#039;s a little antsy and she won&amp;#039;t stay still. Does anyone have any tips? Suggestion: You should play with her like you are grooming constantly. If you are watching tv, put her on your lap and play with her feet, rub [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/funny-dogs-videos/Funny_Dogs_Videos-Grooming_Tips_for_My_Dog.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>I have a yorkshire terrier and of course she needs to be groomed but she&#039;s a little antsy and she won&#039;t stay still. Does anyone have any tips?</p>
<div style="margin:24px 0px 8px 0px;font-weight:bolder;">Suggestion:</div>
<p>You should play with her like you are grooming constantly. If you are watching tv, put her on your lap and play with her feet, rub them between the toes. Do the same with her face. Try combing her when she is relaxed and sitting quietly on your lap. Yorkies are usually antsy, but some extra handling may help her calm down a bit. All this should be done from a very early age to get dogs used to being handled and groomed.</p>
<p><!-- magicrssposts YAHOOANS_qid=20120516123932AANElI6 --></p>
<p>Source: <a href="http://www.funnydogsvideos.com/1728/grooming-tips-for-my-dog/">Grooming Tips for My Dog?</a></p>]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.funnydogsvideos.com/1728/grooming-tips-for-my-dog/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>1</slash:comments>
      <enclosure url="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/funny-dogs-videos/Funny_Dogs_Videos-Grooming_Tips_for_My_Dog.mp3" length="393824" type="audio/mpeg" />
