      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.funnydogsvideos.com/1727/if-a-dog-is-crate-trained-does-that-usually-mean-its-house-trained-to/</guid>
      <description>probably Suggestion: Not necessarily. A dog who is crate trained could be in the process of housebreaking. Crate training is often an effective method of housebreaking a dog but it does NOT imply that they are fully housebroken. Many crate trained dogs do well if you continue with the crate training but will have accidents [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/funny-dogs-videos/Funny_Dogs_Videos-If_a_Dog_is_Crate_Trained_Does_That_Usually_Mean_Its_House_Trained_To.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><p>probably</p>
<div style="margin:24px 0px 8px 0px;font-weight:bolder;">Suggestion:</div>
<p>Not necessarily. A dog who is crate trained could be in the process of housebreaking. Crate training is often an effective method of housebreaking a dog but it does NOT imply that they are fully housebroken. Many crate trained dogs do well if you continue with the crate training but will have accidents if you let them have full run of the house.</p>
<p><!-- magicrssposts YAHOOANS_qid=20120522082034AANoub1 --></p>
<p>Source: <a href="http://www.funnydogsvideos.com/1727/if-a-dog-is-crate-trained-does-that-usually-mean-its-house-trained-to/">If a Dog is Crate Trained Does That Usually Mean Its House Trained To?</a></p>]]></content:encoded>
